result.name: Mirch Masala Indian Restaurant

reviews.text: Terrible food quality, on top of that hygiene issues - found hair in my roti. I am not coming back there ever again — what a waste of time.
did not provide everything offered in the set. we had takeaway and too far to go back to complain. not good portion sizes.
It's great relief to find Indian food and that too it tastes so much like back in India. I would recommend this to anyone looking for Indian food in Hong Kong. And it's easy to find and reach.

Went to Stanley plaza with my friends & as we were walking we saw an Indian restaurant! And it’s something you don’t see often in Hong Kong. The second we entered in the restaurant, the owner and everyone made us feel so welcome :) the owner was talking to us and making sure we felt welcome. He even taught us how to eat Indian food properly! Now the food is AMAZING!!!!!!! The food was tender and juicy. The proportion size is just enough for 6 people (we ordered a 4 people meal) and it was amazing! Everything was amazing, the owner made sure we felt welcome and leaving the restaurant happy:) I’m glad we went here! Also the price is not bad!! Ifs really worth every penny here.

Craving for Indian food.

The Naan is actually bigger here still soft

The portion of vegetable is suitable for 2 Naans
